        <h2 class="subtitle">Non-Fiction Books</h2>
        <ul>
            <li class="content research"><a target="_blank" href="http://amzn.to/2AZGPxU">How Not To Die</a> - Discusses the leading causes of death in the United States, then presents evidence-based research about how each one can be prevented and reversed through a plant-based diet.</li>
            <li class="content research"><a target="_blank" href="http://amzn.to/2zPXSV4">The Plant-Based Journey</a> - Strategies and advice for any aspiring vegan for how to make the switch, plus deep discussion over the WHY behind overeating.</li>
            <li class="content research"><a target="_blank" href="http://amzn.to/2B0JjvV"> - Forks Over Knives: The Plant-Based Way to Health</a>Mix of Science and Recipes</li>
            <li class="content research"><a target="_blank" href="http://amzn.to/2B1rmxA">The China Study</a> - Comprehensive scientific research about the effects of eating animal products on health</li>
            <li class="content research"><a target="_blank" href="http://amzn.to/2yXFcQ3">Prevent & Reverse Heart Disease</a> - Evidence and anecdotes about how patients with cardiovascular diseases can improve their heart health through a plant-based diet, even when they've book told they have less than a year to live.</li>
            <li class="content research"><a target="_blank" href="http://amzn.to/2zhEGjX">The Happy Vegan</a> - Russell Simmons on the physical, mental, and emotional benefits of eating vegan, combined with practical advice on how to manage eating out and social situations.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="subtitle">Cookbooks</h2>
        <ul>
            <li class="content research"><a target="_blank" href="http://amzn.to/2yXP8sC">The Oh She Glows Cookbook</a> - An excellent variety of vegan recipes, complete with stunning pictures.</li>
            <li class="content research"><a target="_blank" href="http://amzn.to/2zfzUUn">But I Could Never Go Vegan!</a> - Comfort foods and classic recipes turned vegan. Instead of trying to imitate a dish normally made with animal products, these meals allow the plants to shine in their own right.</li>
            <li class="content research"><a target="_blank" href="http://amzn.to/2yWSEUc">The Homemade Vegan Pantry</a> - A guide to creating vegan versions of pantry staples--from dairy and meat substitutes such as vegan yogurt, mayo, bacon, and cheese, to dressings, sauces, cookies, and more. </li>
            <li class="content research"><a target="_blank" href="http://amzn.to/2hKvgWJ">Thug Kitchen: The Official Cookbook</a> - The recipes in this book are consistently excellent, but the cooking techniques are complicated and they can take a long time to prepare.</li>
            <li class="content research"><a target="_blank" href="http://amzn.to/2zg6Hsn">Â¡Salud! Vegan Mexican Cookbook</a> - How to make classic Mexican dishes like Enchiladas, Tacos, and Tamales with vegan ingredients.</li>

        </ul>

        <h2 class="subtitle">Documentaries</h2>
        <ul>
            <li class="content research"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1567233/">Forks Over Knives</a> - Research and evidence about reversing degenerative diseases through a diet of plant-based foods.</li>
            <li class="content research"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt3302820/">Cowspiracy</a> - Examines the links between the production of animal products and environmental degradation</li>
            <li class="content research"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt5541848/">What The Health</a> - he sequel from the makers of Cowspiracy tracks the links between animal products and disease, exposing the links between the food industry, government organizations, and health companies.</li>
            <li class="content research"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt6039284/">Food Choices</a> - Explores the impact of food on health, the environment, and more.</li>
            <li class="content research"><a href="https://www.eatingyoualive.com/">Eating You Alive</a> - Investigates how to treat chronic diseases through lifestyle changes and why doctors are not trained in nutrition.</li>
            <li class="content research"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1227378/?ref_=tt_rec_tt">Fat, Sick & Nearly Dead</a> - The inspiring story of an obese Australian man who turns his health around by drinking only fresh fruit and vegetable juice for 60 days.</li>
            <li class="content research"><a target="_blank" href="https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0358456/">Earthlings</a> - Using hidden cameras and never-before-seen footage, Earthlings
                chronicles the day-to-day practices of the largest industries in the world, all of which rely entirely on animals for profit..</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="subtitle">Vegan Cooking Blogs</h2>
        <ul>
            <li class="content research">Not actually a blog but rather a supportive and insightful community, there are many subreddits with advice for aspiring vegans. Be sure to check out<a href="https://reddit.com/r/vegan">/r/vegan</a> for jokes, news, and awesome pictures
                <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/veganfood">/r/VeganFood</a> for recipes, <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/veganfitness">/r/VeganFitness</a> for advice on bulking, cutting, and nutrition for fitness lovers, and
            <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/EatCheapAndVegan/">/r/EatCheapAndVegan</a> for penny pinchers eating vegan.</li>
            <li class="content research"><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/vegan/wiki/beginnersguide">Beginner's Guide To Veganism</a> - A fantastic overview of what it means to be a vegan and responses to common questions regarding plant-based diets.</li>
            <li class="content research"><a href="https://minimalistbaker.com/">Minimalist Baker</a> - Consistently amazing vegan recipes across a wide range of categories, but some of the ingredients may be difficult to find and sometimes fancy kitchen gadgets are required.</li>
            <li class="content research"><a href="http://ohsheglows.com/">Oh She Glows</a> - One of the oldest and most prolific vegan blogs in terms of sheer number of recipes, you can definitely find something to your liking within this deep archive.</li>
            <li class="content research"><a href="https://www.budgetbytes.com/category/recipes/vegetarian/vegan/">Budget Bytes</a> - Not specifically vegan, this website still contains a wide variety of vegan and vegetarian options. The best part is that it's easy to see the cost of each recipe or serving, proving that eating vegan on a budget doesn't mean eating bland.</li>
            <li class="content research"><a href="http://www.veganricha.com/">Vegan Richa</a> - Plenty of delicious recipes across a wide spectrum, although some meals are undeniably complicated. Also a treasure trove of vegan indian recipes.</li>
            <li class="content research"><a href="https://konikoffdental
